A. I Reſerv'd it as the Beſt Wine for the Laſt; For it is indeed moſt often ſo made uſe of in Holy Writing; by Solomon in that moſt Prophetick, Nuptial Song of his, of the Kingdom: by Eſay. c. 62. 5. by Chriſt often; and He makes his Coming to be on purpoſe (
   〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
) [for] the ſake of the Wedding, and not as we Tranſlate, [from] it, Luc. 12. 36. By the Apoſtle Paul Calling it (as the Kingdom is Call'd) Myſtery, Epheſ. 5. 25. 32. By the Apoſtle John in the Prophecy of the Kingdom juſt Appearing, Rev. 19. 7. c. 21. 2. c. 22. 17. And it Carries Great Argument and Inſtruciton.
